*** Masai ***
http://www.seqan.de/projects/masai.html

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Installation
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

This file describes how to compile Masai from source code.
Masai uses SeqAn, the C++ template library for sequence analysis.

To compile Masai follow these steps:

  1. Check-out the svn-trunk version of SeqAn as described here (up to
     "Install"): http://trac.seqan.de/wiki/Tutorial/GettingStarted

  2. Copy the folder with Masai's sources (masai) into the SeqAn
     sandbox directory (seqan-trunk/sandbox)

  3. Follow the "A First Build" step to create a cmake build directory but
     replace "-DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug" by "-DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release"

  4. Compile masai_indexer and masai_mapper, e.g. with
     "make masai_indexer masai_mapper" if you use Makefiles

  5. The binaries will appear in a subfolder of the build directory


